{"version": 2, "width": 100, "height": 30, "timestamp": 1778789166, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "HELIX build: one bounded implementation pass against a governing bead"}
[0.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# Planning is done. A runtime hands the skill a specific bead; build mode runs one bounded implementation pass against the artifacts that govern it.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ ls .ddx/beads.jsonl docs/helix/01-frame/features/\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.4, "o", ".ddx/beads.jsonl\r\ndocs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-001-csv-ingest.md\r\n"]
[1.5, "o", "\r\n\u001b[36m> Use HELIX build mode on bead-001 (CSV header sniffer) in .ddx/beads.jsonl. Read the bead's governing artifacts and acceptance criteria, then execute one bounded implementation pass: write the header sniffer tests, the implementation, and the schema-mapping.yaml. Do not broaden scope beyond bead-001.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.5, "o", "\u001b[2m  \u2699 Skill(skill='helix', args='build mode on bead-001')\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.0, "o", "\u001b[2m  \u2192 Launching skill: helix\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.3, "o", "\u001b[2m  \u2699 Read(file_path='.ddx/beads.jsonl')\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.8, "o", "\u001b[2m  \u2192 bead-001: CSV header sniffer \u00b7 acceptance: schema-mapping.yaml exists; 3 fixtures; go test passes; OWASP A03 clean\u001b[0m\r\n"]
